## Advisory Disposition Gate

If the `/review` result reports all of the following:

- `status.gate_decision = "pass"`
- `status.advisory_count > 0`
- `status.advisory_disposition = null`

do not silently continue to `/qa`. Stop and use AskUserQuestion to make the user choose the
next governed path:

- `fix_before_qa`
  Run:
  ```bash
  {{NEXUS_RUN_COMMAND:build}} --review-advisory-disposition fix_before_qa
  ```
- `continue_to_qa`
  Run:
  ```bash
  {{NEXUS_RUN_COMMAND:qa}} --review-advisory-disposition continue_to_qa
  ```
- `defer_to_follow_on`
  Run:
  ```bash
  {{NEXUS_RUN_COMMAND:qa}} --review-advisory-disposition defer_to_follow_on
  ```

Frame the AskUserQuestion clearly:

> `/review` passed, but it recorded advisories. Choose whether to fix them now or carry them
> forward as non-blocking context.

Recommended ordering:

- A) Fix advisories now
- B) Continue to `/qa`
- C) Defer advisories to follow-on work

If the session is non-interactive, do not call AskUserQuestion. Instead, stop and tell the user
which exact command to run next with the required `--review-advisory-disposition` flag.

If `status.gate_decision = "pass"` and `status.advisory_count = 0`, summarize the clean pass and
offer the canonical next-step choices.

If interactive, use AskUserQuestion:

> `/review` passed cleanly. Choose the next governed step.

- A) Run `/qa` now (recommended)
- B) Run `/ship` now
- C) Stop here

If non-interactive, print the recommended next command:

```bash
{{NEXUS_RUN_COMMAND:qa}}
```

If `status.gate_decision = "fail"`, do not continue to `/qa`. Summarize the blocking findings and,
if interactive, use AskUserQuestion:

> `/review` failed. The canonical next step is a bounded fix cycle through `/build`.

- A) Run `/build` now (recommended)
- B) Stop here
